snippet: The coroner said it was unlikely that the case would ever be resolved, and played down suggestions that facets of Gareth Williams’s private life had led to his death.
abstract: Coroner in London says the death of Gareth Williams, a Welsh-born mathematician involved in top-secret code-breaking work for MI6, found doubled up inside a padlocked duffel bag in his London flat, is unlikely to be solved; suggests that he was unlawfully killed and that some third party was involved.
lead_paragraph: The coroner said it was unlikely that the case would ever be resolved, and played down suggestions that facets of Gareth Williams’s private life had led to his death.

headline.seo: British Spy Most Likely Was Killed, Coroner Says
headline.main: Foul Play Ruled Likely in Case of Spy Found Dead in Bag
headline.print_headline: Foul Play Ruled Likely In Case of Spy Found Dead
